'''Amba''' (also spelled Bulebule, Hamba, Humu, Kihumu, Ku-Amba, Kuamba, Lubulebule, Lwamba, Ruwenzori Kibira, and Rwamba) is a language spoken in parts of [[Uganda]] and the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]] by the [[Amba people]]. The Amba people call it Kwamba and it is known as Kihumu in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. Amba has a 70% lexical similarity with [[Bera language|Bera]]. Dialects include Kyanzi (Kihyanzi) and Suwa (Kusuwa).
There was once an Amba [[pidgin]] called ''Vamba'', now extinct.<ref name="Guthrie" />
